*mb_lcfirst*

(PHP 8 >= 8.4.0)

mb_lcfirst â€” Make a string's first character lowercase

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  mb_lcfirst(string $string, ?string $encoding = null): string~

Performs a multi-byte safe |lcfirst| operation, and returns a string with the
first character of {string} lowercased.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{string}
  The input string.
{encoding}

  The {encoding} parameter is the character encoding. If it is omitted or null,
  the internal character encoding value will be used.

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

Returns the resulting string.

===============================================================================
[ See Also ]

 * |mb_ucfirst| - Make a string's first character uppercase
 * |lcfirst| - Make a string's first character lowercase


